author: Associated Press
title: Dakota protesters set tents on fire as evacuation nears | Daily Mail Online
text: Dakota Access campsite goes up in flames: Protesters set fire to their tents as deadline to evacuate looms and activists warn they are 'ready to go to jail' The Dakota Access pipeline is to be shut down at 2pm local time today Some of the protesters are now burning their tents 'for cultural reasons' The National Guard will enter the camp this afternoon to shut it down Protesters will be offered the choice of either a bus home - or one to jail Authorities say the camp must be vacated because of spring floods Published: 14:51 GMT, 22 February 2017 | Updated: 17:08 GMT, 22 February 2017 46 shares
